# User Journey: Logging Workout and Viewing AI Recommendation

Yannick opens RepRight after arriving at the gym for bench press. He logs his first set: 185lbs for 5 reps. 
The set appears immediately in his history with a yellow-highlighted card. 
He logs two more sets at the same weight. After finishing, he switches to the "Progress & AI" tab to check his progression. 
The app shows a plateau warningâ€”he's been stuck at 185lbs for multiple sessions. 
The AI recommends a deload to 175lbs to help him recover and break through. 
He reviews the reasoning, considering whether to follow the suggestion in his next workout. 
The focused interface keeps him on track without distraction.